<span class="quote">&ldquo;My first &lsquo;encounter&rsquo; with an Alfa (my father&rsquo;s car) was the 1954 Alfa Romeo Giulietta Sprint back in 1965. Black on black, my mind remembers the noice, the smells, the sounds ... too much to handle at a young age.&rdquo;</span> <span class="attrib">&ndash;Miguel Galluzzi (&rsquo;86)</span> 

<span class="quote">&ldquo;The Cord 812 was a game changer &mdash; the boldest, most futuristic, style driven car in its era. The design principles of this vehicle could be applied today and have similar results.&rdquo;</span> <span class="attrib">&ndash;Dave O&rsquo;Connell (&rsquo;80)</span> 

<span class="quote">&ldquo;The simplicity of the wedge form treatment makes the Lancia Stratos look fresh even after a few decades.&rdquo;</span> <span class="attrib">&ndash;Lucian Rosca (&rsquo;89)</span> 

<span class="quote">&ldquo;The 1980 Audi 100 (called the 5000 in the US) was the first true aero sedan with flush glass &mdash; the design that proved aero could be beautiful.&rdquo;</span> <span class="attrib">&ndash;Dave O&rsquo;Connell (&rsquo;80)</span> 

<span class="quote">&ldquo;The 1955-75 Citroen DS was a car ahead of its time in both design and engineering, made when being audacious was part of the DRP and focus groups were not.&rdquo;</span> <span class="attrib">&ndash;Lucian Rosca (&rsquo;89)</span> 

<span class="quote">&ldquo;The 1965 Porsche 911 continues as the sports car reference standard after nearly 50 years. Butzi Porsche&rsquo;s Icon.&rdquo;</span> <span class="attrib">&ndash;Steve Anderson (&rsquo;91)</span> 

<span class="quote">&ldquo;To me there wasn&rsquo;t another car that was as pure, clean, confident, and all around just perfect than the first generation BMW E30 M3 produced from 1985-1992. It wasn&rsquo;t &lsquo;styled&rsquo; but felt just right &mdash; upright, perfectly proportioned, compact and agile.&rdquo;</span> <span class="attrib">&ndash;Robert Bauer (&rsquo;94)</span> 

<span class="quote">&ldquo;The 1973 Ferrari BB512, classical Italian design at its best, represents the end of an era, then came the &lsquo;exuberant&rsquo; 1980&rsquo;s Testarossa.&rdquo;</span> <span class="attrib">&ndash;Miguel Galluzzi (&rsquo;86)</span>

